  "texts": [
    "Expanding Ricci solitons with symmetry 22 7.",
    "Einstein extensions: proof of Theorem G 27 Appendix A. Nilsolitons 27 References 31 IntroductionAn expanding Ricci soliton is a triple (M, g, X) consisting of a complete Riemannian manifold and a vector field that satisfy (1) Ric(g) + 1 2 L X g = -1 2 g, where L denotes the Lie derivative.",
    "Solutions to (1) give rise to self-similar solutions of the Ricci flow: if (η t) t∈R denotes the flow of X, then g(t):= η * t g solves the normalised Ricci flow equation (2) ∂ t g = -2 Ric(g) -g.(Notice that (g(t)) t∈R solves (2) if and only if (ḡ(s):= s • g(log(s))) s∈(0,∞) solves the unnormalised flow.)",
    "Besides generalising Einstein manifolds, and modelling desingularisation of cone-like singularities of the flow [Der16,GS18], these solitons also play a central role in understanding the long-time behavior of Ricci flow solutions that exist for all t ∈ (0, ∞) (immortal solutions).",
    "As shown by the 3D case [Lot10], solitons with constant scalar curvature are particularly relevant."
  ],
